{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-229-four-representations-using-squares","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-201-to-300","demoType":null,"title":"Izazov 229: Reprezentacija četiri korišćenjem kvadrata","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Uzmi broj 3600. Vrlo je jedinstven, jer</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{align}\n&#x26; 3600 = {48}^2 + {36}^2   \\\\\n&#x26; 3600 = {20}^2 + {2×40}^2 \\\\\n&#x26; 3600 = {30}^2 + {3×30}^2 \\\\\n&#x26; 3600 = {45}^2 + {7×15}^2 \\\\\n\\end{align}$$</p>\n<p>Dakle, nalazimo da $88201 = {99}^2 + {280}^2 = {287}^2 + 2 × {54}^2 = {283}^2 + 3 × {52}^2 = {197}^2 + 7 × {84}^2$.</p>\n<p>Godine 1747, Euler je dokazao koji brojevi mogu biti predstavljeni kao zbir dva kvadrata. Zanimljivi su brojevi $n$ koji zadovoljavaju sve četiri sledeće reprezentacije:</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{align}\n&#x26; n = {a_1}^2 + {b_1}^2  \\\\\n&#x26; n = {a_2}^2 + 2{b_2}^2 \\\\\n&#x26; n = {a_3}^2 + 3{b_3}^2 \\\\\n&#x26; n = {a_7}^2 + 7{b_7}^2 \\\\\n\\end{align}$$</p>\n<p>gde su $a_k$ i $b_k$ pozitivni ceo brojevi.</p>\n<p>Postoje brojevi 75373 kao one koje ne prelaze ${10}^7$.</p>\n<p>Koliko je brojeva sličnih koje ne prelaze $2 × {10}^9$?</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f4521000cf542c50ff64","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301872,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-229-four-representations-using-squares"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function representationsUsingSquares() {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\nrepresentationsUsingSquares();","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmiss